A man has been rescued after being thrown off a cliff, Viewpoint at Bridle Road in Kloof.It is reported that the 27-year-old man was thrown over the cliff by four suspects at 8 pm last night.https://www.facebook.com/SAPoliceService/photos/pcb.2006016526091946/2006016386091960/?type=3&#038;theaterhttps://www.facebook.com/SAPoliceService/photos/pcb.2006016526091946/2006016389425293/?type=3&#038;theaterhttps://www.facebook.com/SAPoliceService/photos/pcb.2006016526091946/2006016422758623/?type=3&#038;theaterhttps://www.facebook.com/SAPoliceService/photos/pcb.2006016526091946/2006016432758622/?type=3&#038;theaterAccording to police, the victim was located and found on a ledge 15 meters below the cliff edge. He was found with cable ties around his wrists.The man was stabilized by the paramedics who were on the scene and later transported him to the hospital for further treatment.An attempted murder docket is being investigated by Hillcrest SAPS.-TNA Reporter &nbsp;